
[1]imperative

   IMPER'ATIVE, a. [L. imperativus, from impero, to command. See Empire.]

   1. Commanding; expressive of command; containing positive command, as
   distinguished from advisory, or discretionary. The orders are
   imperative.

   2. In grammar, the imperative mode of a verb is that which expresses
   command, entreaty, advice or exhortation; as, go, write, attend.
